content: Great App!! Question....is there a way to share to someone with an apple device?
replyContent: Yes, use the share data item on the settings page to export your settings to a file that you can email to an apple device.  Open there and select to 'copy to walkout songs' to import it.  The person with the Apple device will need to get the same songs on their device to match with the data as apps sharing music would violate music industry rights.

I'm able to run the majority of that through this app. üëçRecommended. Improvement wish list: - ability to sync with spotify - decrease "fade seconds" minimum to 0 - more main categories/playlists (4 now) - PC compatibility
replyContent: Great feature suggestions...  I do have a few of them already on my todo list and I will add the rest!  Please note the spotify capability is unlikely as Spotify will still not allow integration with a commercial app like mine.  Been trying to convince them for 3 years or so now.

content: Night before tournament weekend and I decided to switch to this app.  In the past I've used instant buttons (Android) to cut & fade music for walk up songs, and In between innings I'd switch over to Amazon music for full length songs.    I was apprehensive about spending $5 since Google play said it may not be compatible with my device, and the fact that the Android version had only been out for a couple weeks.  Definitely buy this app! It's bad ass, and everything I would have hoped it to be.  It replaces 2 apps that I'd use every weekend and rolls it in one, with time and fade adjustments that can be made on the fly without having to recut premade buttons that I had to make the night before.   For all the Android users that are having issues, just buy the songs on Amazon download them then they will be available to use on the app.    Well done!
